[2] Serology, domestic livestock, Jordan, 2013
Date: Thu 12 Dec 2013
Source: Eurosurveillance, Vol 18 (50) [summ., edited]
http://www.eurosurveillance.org/ViewArticle.aspx?ArticleId=20662


Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus (MERS-CoV) serology in major livestock species in an affected region in Jordan, June to September 2013
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Abstract:

Between June and September 2013, sera from 11 dromedary camels, 150 goats, 126 sheep and 91 cows were collected in Jordan, where the 1st human Middle East respiratory syndrome (MERS) cluster appeared in 2012. All sera were tested for MERS-coronavirus (MERS-CoV) specific antibodies by protein microarray with confirmation by virus neutralisation. Neutralising antibodies were found in all camel sera, while sera from goats and cattle tested negative. Although 6 sheep sera reacted with MERS-CoV antigen, neutralising antibodies were not detected.

[Authors: Reusken CB, Ababneh M, Raj VS, Meyer B, Eljarah A, Abutarbush S, Godeke GJ, Bestebroer TM, Zutt I, MÃ¼ller MA, Bosch BJ, Rottier PJ, Osterhaus AD, Drosten C, Haagmans BL, Koopmans MP]

